@Ribby311 I don't necessarily like your line combos haha but I had the same train of thought last week regarding the long-term 2C options vs very short term alternatives.

Simply put, I don't trust any of the popular 2C options out there on a long-term deal.

https://t.co/MEfcBhCnCB

@the_teknic I get your point but it's simply W or bust.

Just gotta wonder if they win, how do you change anything back and eventually it'll catch up.

Cross that bridge when we get there.

@VincentJAccardi Yep.

Point's presence could change that even just a little bit. He's their most dynamic offensive player (not best - most dynamic).

Hey I said it was scorching hot haha

@myownburneracnt And that's a crucial point.

Fox &amp; Kakko are done this summer. Jones too. Laf &amp; Miller done next one. Only Schneider &amp; Nils left for one more year after that (if Nils is here).

Othmann &amp; Berard are coming eventually but next year is last go-around before having to pay the kids.

@thereallj915 So it basically boils down to Kane for a year AND Stastny for 1-2 years then some flexibility

OR

Win a bidding war for one of the popular 2C names floating around and be committed to them for the next 7 years with very little wiggle room unless you move roster pieces out
